com.fluidops.iwb.api.operator

Class Operator

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.fluidops.iwb.api.operator.Operator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class Operator
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    Operator framework for configuration of widgets. Provides convenience method for serialization and evaluation of Operators. The public interface is described by the methods available in the Operator class. Syntax: a) Constant expressions String => 'Hello World' Integer => 1 Double => 1.5 Boolean => true | false Enum => ENUM_VALUE URI => '' Literal => '"MyLiteral"^^xsd:string' b) Lists {{ ITEM1 | ITEM2 | ... | ITEM3 }} c) Structures {{ a = ITEM1 | b = ITEM2 | ... }} d) DYNAMIC Expressions $this.myProperty$ $SELECT ?x WHERE { ?x rdf:type foaf:Person }$ For concrete examples, please refer to the particular OperatorNode implementations in this class, or the test cases. The following special tokens are replaced in constant expressions as well as SELECT queries (see OperatorUtil.replaceSpecialTokens(String) for details): {{Pipe}} => |
